RESTful Services / APIs / Microservices 

Client speaks to server via http protocol. 

Client requests services from server (Representational State Transfer).

Crud Operations: 
  :GET - get data
  :POST - create data
  :PUT - update data
  :DELETE  - get rid of data

http:// <domain> / api / collection (resource, endpoint)  
https:// <domain> / api / collection (resource, endpoint)

GET /api/customers :: req =>  [ { id: 1, name: ''}, { id: 2, name: ''}] :: res 
GET /api/customers/1 => would just return the object 
PUT /api/customers/1 {name: 'Lawrence'} 
POST /api/customers 
DELETE /api/customers/1 
